                          \
    Death Note is one of, if not the best suspense anime ever made. It's fanbase is quite a good indicator of how well this series is written out. Death Note is one of the deepest and exciting anime of recent history., and it brings out a lot of suspense that few might have experienced when watching an anime.\
Story: One of the reasons Death Note is a really popular anime is because of the unique story it offers. It may start simple at first, but as episodes continue to go, you can really get yourself hooked. It starts with Light Yagami, a college student, finds the\
          \
        Death Note and meets his shinigami, Ryuk. Realizing the power in his hands, Light decides to use it to punish criminals and create a world free of evil. Nobody can prevent him from killing criminals, except a detective named L, who becomes his greatest enemy in the course of the series. It starts getting bad, though, during the later part of the series when some changes were made to the cast. That arc really drew out the anime longer, yet it did not have the excitement the first arc really gave the viewers. Still, the story deserves a 10 for the unique way it was presented.\
Art: Art is very well done in the series. The color schemes, the way the characters are drawn, and the appearance of locations in the anime are really good. Death Note offers good effects and lighting which are quite easy on the eyes despite it being one of the darkest and most suspenseful anime out there.\
Sound: The soundtrack fits the series very well, from the opera-style background music to the anime themes. The opening themes really fit the mood of the anime. The first opening sounds like a typical anime theme and it represents Light's ideals and the power he gained from acquiring the Death Note. The second opening though, probably is the most intense anime opening ever made. There were heavy drumming and screams all over the song. This might not please some viewers, but I think it really gave a good representation of the mood of the show at that time, because that is when Light starts his descent into madness due to his power.\
Character: Character design and development are amazing in this anime. You hve Light Yagami, who is a typical college student, who wants to rid the world of evil by using his Death Note. Light acts in a \"The end justifies the means\" way in his quest to purge the world of evil. Next, you have L Lawliet, the world's greatest detective, who is also the person who keeps trying to catch Light as Kira for episode after episode. Those two are probably the most intellectual characters I have seen on an anime. Light has the Death Note and the popularity. L, on the other hand, is highly intelligent and has a lot of connections worldwide.\
Enjoyment: The series is very enjoying in its chess-like element. The series basically comprises of Light and L trying to outsmart each other. L tries to prove that Light is the Kira, while Light tries to prevent himself from being exposed. This anime will keep you on the edge of your seats. The excitement slows down during the second arc, though, with the major character changes made. Still, the first arc more than covers up for it. The anime also presents some questions that makes you question Light's approach. Is it right to deliver a quick justice to criminals by killing them immediately, which by the way, can also be considered murder. Can the criminals not change and not deserve a second chance? Death Note presents such thoughts that make you think deep.\
I would have to agree with the majority in one aspect of this anime: Death Note could very well be the best anime ever made. This anime does not have a typical \"good vs evil\" approach, since both characters can neither be analyzed as good or evil. Light wants to make the world a better place by killing criminals. L is willing to go through extreme measures to stop Light from continuing his work as Kira. The anime is really an intellectual masterpiece, and the realisitc settings would make one wonder if Death Notes really could exist. Death Note is an anime with an effective and unique way of creating anticipation and suspense through its many story plots and how Light and L think of their next move in their battle. Death Note is a top recommedation for anyone wanting to get into anime, and 9 times out of 10, you will not be disappointed. \
