    Ok, so this is my first time writing a review.  I decided to do Death Note just because it was the first alphabetically on my list, lol. There will probably be minor spoilers but nothing major... We'll see. So I guess I'll start with an overall gist I got from the show.\
Death Note is a show about a boy who finds a 'magic' book in his school courtyard... Within the first 5 minutes of the show. When he gets home he reads the inside cover of the book. Apperantly, writing the name of someone kills them. He wants to see if the notebook is\
          \
        just a prank or something, so he picks a mainly small criminal from the news. It works? It does! He decides he wants to be the new 'god' of Earth. And I gotta admit das a pretty c00l goal to get to. But standing in his way is the detective known as 'L'. Shenanigans ensue.\
/STORY- 5 OUTTA 10 EDGES\\\
So I 'summarized' Death Note up there. ^ **Here's where most of the spoilers in this review come in, so you have been warned.** So I thought the story was pretty... Ok? I guess? It's supposed to be a mystery, but I didn't really think it was considering we saw from the antagonist's point of view. I mean, obviously it's the detectives trying to solve the mystery of how so many people are being killed and who's doing it, but it wasn't as engaging as you'd think. Scooby Doo was more engaging than this. Which reminds me- that was one of the things I actually did like about the story- the perspective. I really like how we saw from the 'Bad Guy 2006' perspective. And I know it was supposed to be deep too but it just felt convoluted in the end.\
Oh, did I mention Death Note is separated into 2 parts?\
So we have part 1- which was the summery of what I gave above. It lasted for about 30 episodes or so. BUT then at around ep 30-31, I feel the story became 10x worse. I mean the story was pretty solid up until here. It was like a solid 7-8/10 at least... But it took a turn for the worst. The ladder arc may have been benifited from a 52 episode series- but from what I can tell it may have then been too stretched and filler-y. All in all, the second arc/saga really detracted it for me.\
/ART- 8 OUTTA 10 DEATH POST-IT NOTES\\\
Alright, so the art was pretty 'Anime Standard' if you know what I mean. The art was a little different... But in its own way. Now, this isn't JJBA where the art is super different BUT still manages to look amazing. Basically some scenes make the colors black and white with only the important things vibrantly/saturated color (I.e. Apples, a motif of the show, or hair to represent character) which I liked. The simplicity actually worked very well. But there isn't much more to say, it's a typical 'shonen' art style. It wasn't goofy or anything though- this show did have 'monsters' (I'll get into that in a bit) but the humans did have proper color hair and whatnot (what I mean is this is a shonen technically but it isn't Soul Eater with pink and blue hair). The colors weren't super vibrant, but rather, more of an in between feel that comes from the mid 2000s.\
/SOUND- 7 OUTTA 10 LINKIN PARKS\\\
The sound for this show was pretty average. I find it a bit hard to remember, which means it obviously wasn't 'fantastic' in my opinion. BUT it did sound ominous and fit the feel of the show. The first opening was great. Like without the show I still would have liked it. I don't remember much of the first ending... It was ok I guess. Now the first intro... It's... Special to say the least. The visuals got really spiced up. You could really  feel the show taking a different arc. Ah yes, a less well made op for a less well made arc. Excuse the meme, but it just felt... 'Edgy'. I guess I really don't know how to put it. Same with the second ed. It was ok overall.\
/CHARACTER- 4 OUTTA 10 SHINIGAMI\\\
Characters are where Death Note suffers the most. They just feel... Boring. Boring like the story. Maybe the characters made the story boring? Or was it the story that made the characters boring? So I guess I'll go over them 1 by 1, since I don't really know how to do it otherwise.\
LIGHT 'KIRA' YAGAMI: Bland af. I'm not starting this character list off with him first because he's the main character, no, because he is the WORST character, The thing he suffers from the most is underdevelopment. We don't know who this guy is and where he comes from- he finds the Death Note within the first 5 minutes (maybe not even that) of the series. Did he always have a strong sense of justice? Was he always very intelligent and good at planning? Did he always need to get his cranny in check? These questions don't get answered, so he had no development. And don't even get me started in how he acts in the last episode. But I won't 'spoil' the 'fun'.\
