yeah.\
/ENJOYMENT- 3 SNORING PEOPLE OUTTA 10\\\
As you may be able to tell from that subtitle ^ I found that this show to be extremely boring. Like soooo boring. I literally fell asleep at times. This was one of those shows where you had to watch like 5-10 minutes at a time then give yourself a break because it was that much of a pain. Parts that weren't filler felt like filler, honestly. Now you might be thinking to yourself, or maybe even leaving me a message that says: \"TEHN Y DID U CoNtINU DIS SHO\" Well, I'll answer that. Because everyone was telling me 'oh it's a masterpiece' or 'watching its so well done and deep' and most of all 'death note is really famous get more involved with the community and watch it'. Alright so I'd di all those things, and, sorry, I didn't see it. To me, enjoyment is everything. But wait! You might also be thinking to yourself, \"Is this guy serious right now? He gave Death Note a 5 but SAO a 7 and 9? What the hell is he thinking?\" Well good reader, I will answer that one too. It's because despite how stupid that show was, I at least got a good laugh about it. Hey, at least it kept me awake. All in all, most of Death Note felt like pointless drivel.\
/OVERALL- 5 OUTTA 10 KIND-OF-TRYING-TO-BE-HORROR-BUT-NOT-ACTUALLY-HORROR-ANIMES\\\
\
So, I wouldn't recommend Death Note to many people. I would recommend it to some (I.e. A twelve year old who thinks he's cool) but it's not for everyone. Who knows? Maybe I'm just too dumb to see this was a real masterpiece. My whole problem was the whole second arc, but also how overrated this show was. Seriously. It's been seen as one of the main representatives for years when it doesn't really need that spot. Now, do I think it would have benefited from a sequel? Yeah, definitely. There were many loose ends- maybe not loose ends to say but it just ended ubruptly and was unsatisfactory. Maybe they could have actually shown some backstory in a prequel also. \
