                          \
    Without a doubt, my favorite anime of all time. It holds very close and dear to my heart and always will. It's crazy addictive to watch and is a great psychological thriller! \
Story\
10/10\
Ok, so it's about this guy Light Yagami who finds a Death Note which grants him the power to kill whoever's name is written in it. He uses this to try to purge the world from evil and become a God, but becomes corrupted by power within. He becomes known to the world as Kira and the Japanese police work with investigator L to try and figure out who Kira is and put\
          \
        a stop to his reign of terror. The plot is original and has a great concept that is engaging, interesting, and has a deep message behind it. Which is that power corrupts. And it handles this very well in a way that is mature and effective. And like I said before, it's addictive to watch. The plot becomes quite complicated, but not to the point of being too confusing and leading to frustration. It's more so that it can make you think and try to look back at it. And that's the thing that makes it so addictive to watch. People mostly complain about the second story arc and the ending. I don't care what nobody says, I like it just fine. Without spoiling, the reason it ends this way is to try and get it's point across. And I happen to think it succeeds very well in this aspect. If it were to end differently, it would've been hypocritical towards it's initial goal and it's theme. So don't complain. And as for the second arc in general, I think it's just fine. It doesn't deviate from the story, and it's still just as enjoyable to watch as it was in the first arc. People only complain because of the characters. Can't explain what I mean by that because it would give away major spoilers. So to sum it all up, I love the story and I don't have problems with it like other people seem to.\
Characters\
9.5/10\
The characters for Death Note are great. They are 3 dimensional and well developed. Light Yagami is the villain protagonist that you'll either love or hate, and that's what makes him complex and interesting. L is the heroin antagonist that is the best character of the series. He is similar to Light so much as they are very clever and intelligent and always have tricks up their sleeves. And the fact that they can see right through each others traps is what makes this a fun cat and mouse game. They work off of each other great in their rivalry. Other characters involving Misa, Light's dad, Matsuda, Aizawa, etc are important to the story and serve an important purpose. None of the characters feel out of place or unnecessary. My only criticism is that I don't like how the played the dumb blonde trop with Misa later on. She's a smarter character than that, and I think they just overdid it with that. But still, great characters.\
Animation\
10/10\
The animation is amazing. Distinctive and original character designs especially with L who is practically iconic. Best design out of all of them. The setting is what you'd expect from this kind of anime, but it works great with dark backgrounds that fit the tone of the anime. The Shinigami really stands out as it's creative and has a very cool design. I don't have any problems with the animation at all. It all looks great! The only \"action\" we get is from the deaths themselves which are thrilling and suspenseful like they should. This anime also has a great color scheme using very dark colors as it fits in a very dark anime. Nothing to criticize, so a 10 for me!\
Sound\
10/10 \
Once again, nothing to criticize. The English dub is one of the best dubs out there. One of the few animes out there were the English dub is better than the Japanese dub. Definitely check out the dub! As for the soundtrack, the opening song is one of the best out there. Fits in great with the series. The second one may seem silly with all it's screaming and misheard lyrics, but it's still a great listen. The musical score may be receptive, but only because it's that awesome. Some of the best musical scores I've ever heard in an anime. Seriously worth downloading and listening to causally. So with a great English dub, great musical score, great openings, it's a 10!\
Overall\
9.9/10\
A+\
Death Note is seriously a must watch if you love these kinds of anime, or just anime in general. Once you start watching it, you won't be able to stop. It sucks you in just like that. No other anime has had me this sold on it before. So it's a masterpiece in my book. \
