      text = "                          \
    Death Note’s mainstream appeal is something that clearly has earned the rights to have. It’s easy  to pick up at any point in your life. Well crafted plot twists, great voice acting both sub and dub and clever writing will simply keep your intrested though the entire thing.\
Light Yagami is your everyday high school student till he comes into contact with the death note a magical notebook that can kill anyone by writing their full name in it while picturing their face in which they will simply die of a heart attack in the next 40 seconds. Light’s Descent into madness as he falls\
          \
        for the temptation of the death note with the ideology of becoming the god of the new world in which he strives to create over the course of the show by killing criminals, This capture the attention of the japanese police and later on the world top detective L as they battle Light who has now been dub Kira by socially setting up what could only be described as a game of chess where every major character is nothing more than a pawn in Light’s and L’s battle of wits. \
Every move made by L and Light are logical and are explain well enough for every viewer to follow with ease. Each character remains interesting throughout the entire show as the dynamics of everyone's relationship with each other makes you become attached to everyone of the major players in the story despite not changing all that much throughout the story.\
Sadly the artwork mainly for the backgrounds all just kind of blend together and overall lacks details and soon the animation falls into this problem with many later episodes just being still images and panning shots which if not for the interesting conflicts that come up in the story I would find this show falling into mediocrity which can be a common problem in most animated trillers and dramas. Thankfully the music is great at coavying the tone of the story and the Gothic atmosphere. The World which is the first opening captures Light ascending to godhood and the battle between him and L while What’s up people? Capture Light’s Descent into madness.\
However Death note biggest problem is it second arc which just pulls new characters out of nowheres with nothing interesting about them as the pacing of the show travels at breakneck speeds, the other characters just become boring shells of what they were in the first arc, the writing of the show suffer from the pacing and things are re explain way to much with the only saving grace being that the show animation improves somewhat but at the cost of some episodes becoming more like a action thriller which the show is not supposed to be. The ending of the second arc while having the most over the top laugh scene ever is where the show finally hits rock bottom and kills your enjoyment as a plot twist is just pulled out of nowheres with no foreshadowing or anything.\
Overall the show is not flawless but it’s worth watching the first arc for the tightly constructed plot and character dynamics, the themes of ideological conflicts, godhood and temptation as well as being understandable for everyone no matter their age though the use of clever writing, while the second arc is poorly constructed it’s still entertaining mainly to see how fast the arc can hit rock bottom for yourself ",
