\
                          \
    Story: 9\
Art: 10\
Sound: 10\
Character: 9\
Enjoyment: 10\
Overall: 10\
Do I even need to say anything more? Well I will. Death Note is by far my favorite anime, is it perfect? No, of course not. Nothing is perfect and like all anime, Death Note is not flawless. I'm guessing you've already heard people pointing out everything they love about it so before I jump on the bandwagon and do the same, let me point out the only two flaws I can think of so that I don't seem too biased.\
1. Characters. \"But wait a minute, you gave character a 9/10, isn't that really good?\" Yes, but it's not\
          \
        without it's problems. Remember, right now I'm only focusing on the bad aspects of this show, the good parts come later. Many of the characters are only there to move the plot forward, Misa is a prime example of this, she is basically a plot device with no character development, and this applies to almost all characters (except  maybe Matsuda who ironically enough is a comic relief character)\
2. The last third of the series. This is probably the most common complaint from people who didn't like Death Note. The last 12 episodes of this 37 episode series are not as good as the previous 25 due to reasons I will not reveal because BBCode is diabled. Let's just say felt unneccesary, were is not for the brilliant/awful ending. Personally I don't dislike these last few episodes as much as most people do but I can at least see why they do.\
Now, for the praise. Here's a tl;dr version of it: It's REALLY good.\
There are several characters in Death Note but you only need to care about two of them, Light and L. They both steal the show with their brilliant scheming, amazing deductive abilities and just all around enjoyable personalities. Light (the MAIN-main character) is actually a villain, something that's rarely seen in anime. \"But One Piece is about pirates, aren't they villains?\" No, because they don't do things like kill innocent people just because they stand in the way of justice (or at least Lights personal view of justice). He lies, manipulates people and is overall just a big douche... and I love it. Unlike most other anime villains we actually get to see Light plan for his evil... plans. Being an evil genious is not as easy as one might think and Light goes through a lot of hardships for the sake of his ambition to create a perfect world (and rule it as a God). He is calm, collected and does everything as smoothly as possible while trying to hide that evil grin of his, he is just too much fun to watch.\
But every hero needs a villain... which in this case is a hero... anyway, it's L. L is the worlds most brilliant detective and a perfect opponent for Light. He's a weird, eccentric, creepy, sugar addicted and overall socially awkward person with a skin so pale it makes Edward from Twiligt look normal. He's also impartial and daring devoting everything towards catching Light, it's a great cat and mouse thriller with no dull moments, which is quite an accomplishment considering the show is 90% dialogue.\
\"Wait... what?\" Yeah, that's right. While Death Note does have a few action scenes it's mostly just filled with dialogue, or should I say monologue. But unlike anime like Bakemonogatari which is filled with lots of entertaining dialogue which then ultimately lead nowhere all the dialogue in Death Note matters, better yet, it makes you feel really smart for no reason which is why many call Death Note an intelligent anime. This unfortunately is false, just because you're watching a complicated story with lots of twist and turns it doesn't mean that you are an intelligent person. Everything is explained in great detail and the only thing you have to do as a viewer is to sit back and enjoy the ride. Another popular misconception is that a lot of people seem to think that Death Note deals with important issues like \"Is it right to kill criminals?\" Death Note however, does not. It simply brings these issues to the table, but it doesn't do anything with them. Light quickly comes to the conslusion that \"Yes, it is\" and it's not really discussed a lot in the series after that.\
The art and music in this series is also wonderful and they fit perfectly together, to explain why would be pointless when you can just watch this video instead: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G4LvpibQ_-E\
And now we're at the end of this review. Usually this is the part when I'm suppposed to write something like \"all in all Death note is a very good anime that dwelves deep into the bla bla bla\" but as you can see I'm not going to do that. Instead I'm going to leave you with these 59 words that I hope you'll find very useful: WATCH DEATH NOTE NOW IT IS A REALLY GOOD ANIME AND I BET YOU WILL LIKE IT WAIT WHY AM I WRITING WITH CAPS LOCK ON OH WELL IT IS TOO LATE TO TURN IT OFF NOW WHAT WAS I TALKING ABOUT AGAIN OH YEAH DEATH NOTE YOU SHOULD GO WATCH IT YOU WILL NOT REGRET IT I PROMISE\
