    [633] = {
      score = 9,
      text = "\
                          \
    Hello fellow Otakus  and welcome to my Review of Death Note!\
Death Note is a 37 Episode Anime Series Animated by Madhouse Studios from 2006-2007.\
Story:\
The Story for Death Note is brilliant and Original. Presenting intriguing situations for Light to experience, the Mystery setting is very well done with very serious and Dramatic moments. Actually everything is dramatic in Death Note even eating Potato Chips. Now to talk about the 2nd half of the show, a lot of people seem to hate it saying its dull and that the show should have ended sooner, I however disagree, I had no problems at all with the 2nd\
          \
        half, did I prefer the 1st half? Yes, but did I think that the 2nd half was bad? Not at all. But yeah the Story is very well written and keeps you on the edge of your seat for the entire duration of the show.\
Characters:\
Death Note presents you with some great characters, the focus of the show is on them, and the series wouldn’t have worked as well as it did if they hadn’t been presented the way they were. Now lets take a look at the main cast.\
1st you have Light Yagami, the lead character of the series, he is intelligent as all hell, he is always out smarting the enemy and even when you think he can’t find his way out of a situation, he comes up with a way that you never would have thought of. He was a great anti-hero of a main character and by far my favorite of the bunch.\
Next up is Ryuk, he is the one responsible for the Death Note coming in contact with Light. If he hadn’t dropped it into the human world there would be no series, therefore you would be doing more important things right now than reading my Review.\
Next on the list is L, L is a detective who is almost, if not, as intelligent as Light, most of the time you can’t figure out who is going to do what its very unpredictable because L is such a good match for Light. Now, a lot of people say L is their favorite character, mostly fan girls who squeal every time he’s on screen and although Light is my favorite Character, at first I had a hard time deciding who I liked more L or Light, it was difficult until the 2nd half of the series.\
Now we get to Misa, who is essentially the love interest for Light but really isn’t, because she wants the D while Light couldn’t care less, so it’s really that Light is her love interest. She also has a really dark back story, which I will not spoil in case you haven’t seen the series.\
And finally we get to Near, who to most people their most hated character in the show. He is the reason the 2nd half is hated, I personally, like I said before, enjoyed the 2nd half and I liked Near he wasn’t nearly as good as L but was still a nice match for Light.\
Sound:\
Death Note was English Dubbed by Viz Media and I have to say they did a great job, I think all of the actors did a really good job in their roles especially Brad Swaile as Light. The sound track is great providing dramatic music to make things more exciting during scenes that might otherwise be boring, the openings and endings are really good, Personally my favorite of them all is the 1st opening \"The World\" by Nightmare, being one of my favorite openings for an Anime Evar! So, there were no problems with the sound of this show.\
Final Score:\
Taking all of this information into account I give Death Note a 9/10 for being a great Dramatic Mystery show that anyone can watch and enjoy. That’s all for now, hope you liked my Review!",
      helpful = 3,
    },
