      text = "\
                          \
         This is an excellent concept that had unlimited potential.  The power of judgment via death is given to the brightest young mind in Japan and his ridiculously in-depth strategies to remake the world in his image and avoid capture.  The antagonist is one of the most finely tuned and fascinatingly entertaining characters I have encountered  -  the great detective L.\
     I will do my best to not put spoilers in my reviews but let it be known that about 2/3 through this series it's intrigue and glory start to fade...culminating with a two-part ending\
          \
        episode that....well it ruined the show in my opinion.  Completely wrecking a prime character was more of a 'Well....we....we should probably finish this thing shouldn't we?' feeling than the more appropriate 'How should these events play out in the circumstances?' method.\
     All in all  -  worth watching, the English dub (if that's your thing *shudders*) isn't too bad ... at least until they introduce a character near the end...where the translation and execution of the lines made me quite furious at the actors take on it.  I highly recommend the original Japanese audio (as I am wont to do) however.  Nightmare and Maximum the Hormone's music adds perfect touches to the opening and end credits  -  wrapping this up in a neat little macabre package.",
