    },
    [729] = {
      score = 10,
      text = "\
\
\
                          \
    You ever wish for an anime that surprises you and gives you enjoyment overall? Death Note is the anime for you, it's by far an outstanding anime in nearly every prospect, but many people feel light hearted when it comes to this show, many thing it's a bad ass horror, but it's actually more of a thriller.\
This was the first anime I watched, back when YouTube was all retro, retro meaning when anything could be uploaded about 6 years ago. I have watched it several times since, thus it's not out of my mind. It was quite weird looking back that it was my first\
          \
        anime because of the genre of anime, many people starting anime would have been watching the big three or from watching animated movies such as Spirited Away or Mononoke Hime, but it was different, it was unique and most of all, it was brilliant.\
The story begins as Yagami Light, a highschool student, son of a detective. Baring hate to this world, one day he's staring out a window and catches a book falling from the sky, his attention is then put onto the book, from which he takes it home, and from there he finds out it's purpose. the book is called the \"Death Note\" and simply put, when you write a name into it, they die. The main requirement for killing is, you need to know their name and their face in order to kill them, and you can specify how they die.\
The Death Note origins: The book is a book of the Death Gods (Shinigami), they use these to keep an eye on the real world, Ryuk, the owner of the death note Light picks up comes down from the limbo like world to find the book, but to find a human has found it, which he sticks around to see what the human does, thinking much will not come from him. When you touch the book, you are able to see the owner of the book (Death God), thus when Light touched it, he was able to see Ryuk, only because he is the owner of that book.\
Since Light hates the current world, he wants to free the world from despair and rid it of all the inconsistencies and become god of it. He sets out killing people whom have committed crimes of mass load. But after so many people dying, a special detective is called in, the best of the best, his name is simply \"L\", nothing more, nothing less, and nobody knows his identity. His job is to catch Kira, Kira being the holders of the Death Notes, Light went with it after fans went about calling him Kira online.\
Many openings open up and many new characters come in, expanding the show and the entertainment from it, the art of this show is great, but not outstanding as it's not the newest of animes. the Sounds are awesome, insert songs are to die for, awesome riffs. Openings and Endings are perfect, Both Artists whom did them \"Nightmare\" and \"Maximum the Hormone\", were one of the first bands to get me into Japanese music. One being a japanese metal group and the other being rock, it's quite different, but good.\
Conclusion, by now, you should see that this anime is awesome, everything is pretty much perfect, right down to the characters, nearly everyone will like this show, I won't lie about that, but as per usual you do get the odd case of people not liking things, be that it's not their genre, or it's a fad.\
Signing off, go watch it, it's a great anime, you won't waste your time with it.\
It's very enjoyable and the rewatch value is quite good.",
